EDUCATIONAL USE DISCLAIMER

This repository contains academic research on hardware virtualization techniques
and digital rights management (DRM) bypass methods. The information provided is
intended solely for:

1. Educational purposes in computer security research
2. Understanding modern anti-tamper protection mechanisms
3. Security vulnerability disclosure and analysis
4. Academic advancement of virtualization technology

The authors and contributors explicitly DO NOT condone:
- Software piracy or copyright infringement
- Illegal circumvention of copy protection systems
- Distribution of cracked software or game cracks
- Use of this information for commercial piracy

This research is provided under the principle of fair use for academic and
security research purposes. Users are responsible for complying with all
applicable laws, including the Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) and
equivalent international legislation.

By accessing this repository, you agree to use the information responsibly and
ethically, respecting intellectual property rights and software licenses.

For responsible disclosure of security vulnerabilities discovered through this
research, please contact the affected software vendors directly through their
established vulnerability reporting channels.

